                <h1>Discover Gothic Architecture: A Historical Overview</h1>
                <p>Gothic architecture emerged in the 12th century in France and flourished until the 16th century, characterized by pointed arches, ribbed vaults, and flying buttresses. This style aimed to create height and light, resulting in grand cathedrals like Notre-Dame. It reflects the cultural, artistic, and religious aspirations of the medieval period.</p>
